<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1313595-is-watching-the-movie-a-substitute-for">Is watching the movie a substitute for reading it? 

I just start reading first 10 pages and decided to watch a movie. After watching it, I really can feel how interesting/exotic life at that time. in that region in China was, also how terrific the extreme of the movie reveals (sex, killing, man vs woman). 

I am a bit scared that reading leaves too much of an negative feeling on me. Any opinions?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1313595'><a id="like_count_community_question_1313595" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1313595?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">1 like</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F16125177-red-sorghum">like</a></span>

</li>
