          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780140168549" href="/book/show/894154.Red_Sorghum">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer724278931" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8779896652238494790">I liked this book which takes place mostly in the 1930&apos;s and revolves around a family of people who depend on sorghum for most of their livelihood. A huge supporting cast made up of Chinese nationalists, communists, warlords and Japanese invaders makes for a lot of spilled blood which, like the sorghum, is red; lots of red. Still, as in life, there is humor, love/lust, tragedy and plain hard work, (but mostly tragedy). I was glad to finish the book but also to have read it. Believable historical</span>
  <span id="freeText8779896652238494790" style="display:none">I liked this book which takes place mostly in the 1930's and revolves around a family of people who depend on sorghum for most of their livelihood. A huge supporting cast made up of Chinese nationalists, communists, warlords and Japanese invaders makes for a lot of spilled blood which, like the sorghum, is red; lots of red. Still, as in life, there is humor, love/lust, tragedy and plain hard work, (but mostly tragedy). I was glad to finish the book but also to have read it. Believable historical fiction. </span>
