<div id="review_3281286813" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3281286813" />
    <a title="Alice Turner" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/49308576-alice-turner"><img alt="Alice Turner" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1448238044p2/49308576.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3281286813?book_show_action=true">Jan 15, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Alice Turner" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Alice Turner" href="/user/show/49308576-alice-turner">Alice Turner</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780140168549" href="/book/show/894154.Red_Sorghum">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3281286813" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13973028394583528992">This book is beautiful and awful at the same time. It took me most of 2020 to read as I kept abandoning it because of the extreme violence. Every possible horror that could be acted on man, woman, child or beast occurs in this novel. It is not for the faint-hearted. Saying that, it is beautifully written and there was never any question of abandoning it completely. It depicts the visceral, bloody, violent cycle of life in a small area of China during war times, set amongst the red sorghum planta</span>
  <span id="freeText13973028394583528992" style="display:none">This book is beautiful and awful at the same time. It took me most of 2020 to read as I kept abandoning it because of the extreme violence. Every possible horror that could be acted on man, woman, child or beast occurs in this novel. It is not for the faint-hearted. Saying that, it is beautifully written and there was never any question of abandoning it completely. It depicts the visceral, bloody, violent cycle of life in a small area of China during war times, set amongst the red sorghum plantations. The story jumps about from generation to generation and back again. It combines mostly gritty social realism with occasional flourishes of magical realism. It is a book that will definitely stay with me. </span>
  <a data-text-id="13973028394583528992" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


